<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="34" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="37.[1241,2106,1380,1797]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">
<taxonomicName box="[1244,1338,1380,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Tachys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1244,1338,1380,1410]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">Tachys</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName authority="Schaum 1863: 89" authorityName="Schaum" authorityPageNumber="89" authorityYear="1863" box="[1359,1720,1380,1410]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turgidus">turgidus Schaum 1863:89</taxonomicName>
. [Type missing from 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2060,2102,1380,1410]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">the</emphasis>
point; lost in mail during transport to J. Negre, 
<emphasis box="[1965,2101,1418,1448]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">December</emphasis>
1963, according to Hieke's note on pin in HUB. Neotype, female, here selected from MCZ material determined by 
<emphasis box="[1272,1317,1533,1563]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">Van</emphasis>
Emden, who undoubtedly saw the type. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1907,2092,1533,1563]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">Type-locality</emphasis>
: Originally &quot;Brasilia,&quot; according to Schaum and labels, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2057,2103,1571,1601]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">but</emphasis>
herewith restricted 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1568,1594,1609,1639]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">to</emphasis>
Nova 
<taxonomicName box="[1716,1843,1609,1639]" class="Arachnida" family="Teutoniidae" genus="Teutonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Teutonia</taxonomicName>
, Santa 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">Catarina, Brazil</emphasis>
, from labels appearing 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1700,1734,1648,1678]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">on</emphasis>
selected 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1869,1980,1648,1678]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">neotype</emphasis>
.] DESCRIPTION.—Form: As in 
<taxonomicName box="[1822,2101,1709,1746]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laevimicans">
<emphasis box="[1822,1852,1709,1746]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">X</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1899,2101,1710,1746]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">laevimicans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2101,2106,1710,1746]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="38" lastPageNumber="35" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="37.[1241,2106,1380,1797]" box="[1242,2104,1757,1794]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">Easily distinguished from all other species in the</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828584" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3828584" box="[840,1585,2673,2703]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828584/files/figure.png" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" startId="37.[840,931,2673,2703]" targetBox="[527,1888,1841,2662]" targetPageId="37">
<paragraph box="[840,1585,2673,2703]" pageId="37" pageNumber="34">
FIGURE 69.—Approximate range of the 
<taxonomicName box="[1412,1478,2673,2703]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Xystosomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="34" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gruti">gruti</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">group by the absence of lateral setigerous pores at the hind angles of the pronotum together with the obtuse hind angles of the pronotum.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Color: Head and forebody rufopiceous; elytra usually darker; pronotum and elytra moderately iridescent; appendages testaceous; antennae slightly infuscated apically.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Head: Broad between eyes; frontal furrows shal- lowly impressed, straight, posteriorly divergent; eyes small, large-faceted, slightly prominent.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[548,709,947,984]" captionStart="FIGURES 57-62" captionStartId="34.[538,640,2583,2614]" captionTargetBox="[303,2064,1685,2535]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 57-62.—Pronotum, dorsal aspect: 57, Xystosomus laevis, female, Nova Teutonia, Brazil; 58, X.paralaevis, female, Sao Paulo, Brazil; 59, X. laevimicans, female, Santos, Brazil; 60, X. niger, female, Serra Bocaina, Brazil; 61, X. tholus, male, Alto da Serra, Brazil; 62, X. turgidus, female, Rio Caraguata, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828580" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828580/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Figure 62</figureCitation>
): Broadly transverse (W/L, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[307,328,993,1030]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">x</emphasis>
1.75; range, 1.62-1.86; 18 specimens); 
<emphasis box="[975,1185,993,1030]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">anterior pair</emphasis>
of lateral setigerous pores present at apical third, posterior pair absent; laterobasal 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[950,1069,1084,1121]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">carinae</emphasis>
rudi- mentary; hind angles sharp, obtuse, sides anterior to angles more or less straight; side margins beaded, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,365,1222,1259]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">not</emphasis>
reflexed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[349,465,1271,1307]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Elytra:</emphasis>
Smooth; seta Eo4 in position d 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1082,1181,1270,1307]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">rather</emphasis>
than 
<emphasis box="[402,419,1316,1353]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">c</emphasis>
; plica small, evident externally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" box="[350,973,1363,1400]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[350,687,1363,1400]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Microsculpture: As</emphasis>
in 
<figureCitation box="[751,967,1363,1400]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="18.[525,616,2546,2575]" captionTargetBox="[491,1943,485,2524]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="FIGURE 22.—Scanning electron micrographs (X125O) of dorsal microsculpture. Xystosomus gruti: a, frons; b, pronotal disc; c, disc of left elytron; note serial puncture. Xystosomus turgidus: d, frons; e, pronotal disc; /, disc of left elytron. Xystosomus ovatulus: g, disc of left elytron; note serial puncture." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3828543" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3828543/files/figure.png" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">
Figure 
<emphasis box="[872,917,1364,1400]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">22</emphasis>
d,e
</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" box="[350,1184,1409,1446]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis box="[350,524,1410,1446]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Secondary</emphasis>
sexual 
<emphasis box="[682,872,1410,1446]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">characters:</emphasis>
Male 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1019,1174,1409,1446]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">unknown</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">
Female genitalia characteristic of the species group. 
<emphasis box="[350,431,1502,1538]" italics="true" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">Size:</emphasis>
Eighteen specimens: length, 2.0-2.4 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1107,1171,1501,1538]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">mm</emphasis>
;
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="38.[306,1185,484,1814]" box="[313,641,1547,1584]" pageId="38" pageNumber="35">width, 1.0-1.2 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
